The paper discusses a new reading comprehension benchmark that requires systems to perform discrete operations over the content of paragraphs, which involves a more comprehensive understanding of the content than prior datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural networks (cs.NE).
